, and distinguished from all other species of the genus by possessing a frontal squamation pattern consisting of one scale with all margins exposed just posterior to snout (
<emphasis id="B90F3738FF80FF97FD07FC24FCAAFC00" box="[765,794,995,1018]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">vs.</emphasis>
scale with all margins exposed near the center of median portion of frontal region) and an oblique infraorbital dark gray bar through chin (
<emphasis id="B90F3738FF80FF97FEA9FB84FEC0FBA0" box="[339,368,1091,1114]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">vs.</emphasis>
never a similar color pattern). Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B90A9FF80FF97FF6DFBA4FEB1FB80" authorityName="Garman" authorityYear="1895" box="[151,257,1123,1146]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="atratus">
<emphasis id="B90F3738FF80FF97FF6DFBA4FEB1FB80" box="[151,257,1123,1146]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">R. atratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B90A9FF80FF97FEF5FBA4FECFFB80" authorityName="Garman" authorityYear="1895" box="[271,383,1123,1146]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ornatus">
<emphasis id="B90F3738FF80FF97FEF5FBA4FECFFB80" box="[271,383,1123,1146]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">R. ornatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B90A9FF80FF97FE4EFBA4FDABFB80" authorityName="Costa" authorityYear="2003" box="[436,539,1123,1146]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="romeri">
<emphasis id="B90F3738FF80FF97FE4EFBA4FDABFB80" box="[436,539,1123,1146]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">R. romeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and distinguished from the remaining congeners by having fewer anal-fin rays (8-10, vs. 11-19). Distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B90A9FF80FF97FE13FB64FDE0FB40" authorityName="Costa" authorityYear="2003" box="[489,592,1187,1210]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="romeri">
<emphasis id="B90F3738FF80FF97FE13FB64FDE0FB40" box="[489,592,1187,1210]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">R. romeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B90A9FF80FF97FDA4FB64FD7EFB40" authorityName="Garman" authorityYear="1895" box="[606,718,1187,1210]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ornatus">
<emphasis id="B90F3738FF80FF97FDA4FB64FD7EFB40" box="[606,718,1187,1210]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">R. ornatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B90A9FF80FF97FCF9FB64FF53FB20" authorityName="Garman" authorityYear="1895" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="atratus">
<emphasis id="B90F3738FF80FF97FCF9FB64FF53FB20" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">R. atratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a marginal dark reddish brown stripe on the caudal fin in males (
<emphasis id="B90F3738FF80FF97FE53FB24FE77FB00" box="[425,455,1251,1274]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">vs.</emphasis>
dark marginal stripes absent). Differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B90A9FF80FF97FED4FAC4FE2BFAE0" authorityName="Garman" authorityYear="1895" box="[302,411,1283,1306]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="atratus">
<emphasis id="B90F3738FF80FF97FED4FAC4FE2BFAE0" box="[302,411,1283,1306]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">R. atratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B90A9FF80FF97FE2CFAC4FDF9FAE0" authorityName="Garman" authorityYear="1895" box="[470,585,1283,1306]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ornatus">
<emphasis id="B90F3738FF80FF97FE2CFAC4FDF9FAE0" box="[470,585,1283,1306]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">R. ornatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of dermosphenotic (
<emphasis id="B90F3738FF80FF97FEA9FAE4FEC0FAC0" box="[339,368,1315,1338]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">vs.</emphasis>
presence), absence of preopercular canal absent (
<emphasis id="B90F3738FF80FF97FEEDFA84FE84FAA0" box="[279,308,1347,1370]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">vs.</emphasis>
conspicuous short canal), and frontal scales arranged transversally (
<emphasis id="B90F3738FF80FF97FE6AFAA4FE1DFA80" box="[400,429,1379,1402]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">vs.</emphasis>
circularly). Differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B90A9FF80FF97FD4CFAA4FCA9FA80" authorityName="Costa" authorityYear="2003" box="[694,793,1379,1402]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="romeri">
<emphasis id="B90F3738FF80FF97FD4CFAA4FCA9FA80" box="[694,793,1379,1402]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">R. romeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having short anal fin, its tip reaching vertical through caudal peduncle (
<emphasis id="B90F3738FF80FF97FC03FF04FBA6FF20" box="[1017,1046,195,218]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">vs.</emphasis>
long anal fin in males, tip teaching vertical through caudal-fin base), 32 scales on the longitudinal series (
<emphasis id="B90F3738FF80FF97FC76FEC4FC19FEE0" box="[908,937,259,282]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">vs.</emphasis>
29-30), 16 scale rows around caudal peduncle (
<emphasis id="B90F3738FF80FF97FA5FFEC4FA72FEE0" box="[1445,1474,259,282]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">vs.</emphasis>
12), and six branchiostegal rays (
<emphasis id="B90F3738FF80FF97FB66FEE4FB09FEC0" box="[1180,1209,291,314]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">vs.</emphasis>
five).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C361B8A1FF80FF94FCBAFEA5FED5FB43" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC4EB2AFF80FF97FCBAFEA5FC2CFD80" blockId="1.[832,1475,354,1434]" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis id="B90F3738FF80FF97FCBAFEA5FC79FE80" bold="true" box="[832,969,354,378]" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">Description.</emphasis>
Morphometric data given in Table 1. Male larger than female, largest male 
<quantity id="4C8346CFFF80FF97FBB7FE44FB1AFE60" box="[1101,1194,387,410]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.27" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="22.7">22.7 mm</quantity>
SL. Dorsal profile slightly convex from snout to end of dorsal-fin base, approximately straight on caudal peduncle. Ventral profile convex on head, almost straight from anterior portion of venter to end of analfin base, nearly straight on caudal peduncle. Body slender, subcylindrical anteriorly, slightly wider than deep, to compressed posteriorly. Greatest body depth at level of pelvicfin base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC4EB2AFF80FF97FC9FFD44FC42FC20" blockId="1.[832,1475,354,1434]" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">Tip of dorsal fin rounded. Tip of anal fin slightly pointed in male, rounded in female. Caudal fin oval. Pectoral fin rounded, posterior margin on vertical anterior to pelvic-fin base. Tip of pelvic fin reaching between base of 1st and 3rd anal-fin ray in male, and urogenital opening in female. Pelvicfin bases in close proximity. Dorsal-fin origin on vertical through base of 8th or 9th anal-fin ray, and between neural spines of 19th and 20th vertebra. Anal-fin origin between pleural ribs of 14th and 15th vertebra. Dorsal-fin rays 6-7; anal-fin rays 9-10; caudal-fin rays 23; pectoral-fin rays 15; pelvic-fin rays 6.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC4EB2AFF80FF97FC9FFC24FB74FAE0" blockId="1.[832,1475,354,1434]" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">Scales large, cycloid. Trunk entirely scaled; head scaled, except in anterior ventral surface. Few scales on caudal-fin base; no scales on dorsal and anal fins. Frontal squamation comprising scales arranged in transverse pattern, each scale with exposed posterior margin, except scale just posterior to snout with all borders free; E-scales not overlapping medially. Longitudinal series of scales 32; transverse series of scales 7; scale rows around caudal peduncle 16. Cteniilike contact organ in each scale of ventral portion of male flank. Supraorbital neuromasts 3+3.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC4EB2AFF80FF94FC9FFAE4FA18FF00" blockId="1.[832,1475,354,1434]" lastBlockId="2.[839,1482,194,250]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">
Basihyal subtriangular, greatest width about 40 % of length; basihyal cartilage about 25 % of basihyal length. Interhyal vestigial, not ossified. Six branchiostegal rays. Second pharyngobranchial teeth absent. Gill-rakers of first 
<emphasis id="B90F3738FF83FF94FCBDFF05FC7CFF20" bold="true" box="[839,972,194,218]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named in honor of the biologist Alexandre Kirovsky, collector of most specimens of the 
<typeStatus id="54C05588FF83FF94FAD5FF24FAEDFF00" box="[1327,1373,227,250]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">type</typeStatus>
series.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF04BBA2FF80FF97FF6DF865FBCEF843" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5416932" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5416932" box="[151,1150,1954,1978]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5416932/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" startId="1.[151,190,1954,1978]" targetBox="[151,1475,1531,1861]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph id="8BC4EB2AFF80FF97FF6DF865FBCEF843" blockId="1.[151,1150,1954,1978]" box="[151,1150,1954,1978]" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis id="B90F3738FF80FF97FF6DF865FF6CF840" bold="true" box="[151,220,1954,1978]" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">Fig. 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C7B90A9FF80FF97FF1BF864FE25F840" authorityName="Costa" authorityYear="2004" box="[225,405,1955,1978]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kirovskyi">
<emphasis id="B90F3738FF80FF97FF1BF864FE25F840" box="[225,405,1955,1978]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">Rivulus kirovskyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, holotype, UFRJ 5935, male, 20.3 mm SL; Brazil: Amazonas: Manaus.
</paragraph>
